    "Next, two priors are calculated before running Starfysh, including a prior for the cell state proportions that reflects their spot enrichment and a prior for the library size:",
    "Prior for the cell type proportion:",
    "A(x i, s k) is defined as the enrichment score 74 of the marker genes for cell state k at spot i.",
    "The score is first calculated with the Scanpy function 'scanpy.tl.score_genes', which computes the marker genes' average expression and subtracts from it the average expression of a reference gene set G′ randomly sampled from binned expressions:",
    "∑ g∈G ′ x ig."
